original: Håkanson, Gustaf Julius Emanuel, advokat, Göteborg, f. 25/11/79 i Ös’ter-sund av Julius H. o. Märta Brita Tho-rén. G. 12 m. Onrii Johansson. Barn: Marta f. 13, Gösta 16. — Mog:ex. i Visby 00, prel:ex. i Upps. 01, hovr:ex. 05. E. o. not. i Svea hovr. 05, tings-tjg. i Piteå 07-09, tf. borgm. där 07, tjg. v. prot. i Svea hovr. höstsess. 09-11, därunder tidvis förordn. som bitr. fiskal, inneh. tillf, uppdrag i vattenf :-styr. 11, anst. å H. Wikströms Adv:-byrå i Gbg 12-15, därefter egen adv:-verksamh. där. Led. av Sv:es adv:-samf. sed. 29. Skr.: Skall partiintresset dominera över nationens intresse v. rösträttsfrågans avgörande? (07), Sv:es folk inför en ny refoirmation (35).
translated: Håkanson, Gustaf Julius Emanuel, lawyer, Gothenburg, born November 25, 1879 in Östersund to Julius H. and Märta Brita Thorén. Married Onrii Johansson in 19xx. Children: Marta born in 1913, Gösta born in 1916. Completed the bar exam in Visby in 1900, preliminary law exam in Uppsala in 1901, appellate court exam in 1905. Became a deputy notary in the Svea Court of Appeal in 1905, served as a court clerk in Piteå from 1907-1909, acting mayor there in 1907, worked as a clerk in the Svea Court of Appeal during the autumn session from 1909-1911, occasionally serving as an assistant prosecutor with temporary assignments in the water board from 1911. Employed at H. Wikström's law firm in Gothenburg from 1912-1915, then started his own law practice there. Became a member of the Swedish Bar Association in 1929. Author of "Should party interests dominate over the nation's interest in determining suffrage?" (1907) and "Sweden's people facing a new reformation" (1935).
